The paper discusses the challenges of delivering real-time multimedia traffic over wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked multimedia (cs.MM) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive controls and transmission rate control, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computer architecture (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of automatic repeat request (ARQ) for error control, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
